# Shopping Frequency vs Subscription Status


## 1. Customer Loyalty vs Subscription
This chart compares shopping frequency (a measure of customer loyalty) with subscription status. 
Across all categories—from annual to weekly shoppers—non-subscribers consistently make up the larger portion. 
This indicates that many loyal, repeat customers are not enrolled in the subscription program.

## 2. Key Finding
There is no significant difference showing that higher shopping frequency leads to higher subscription rates. 
Even among the most frequent shoppers, the proportion of subscribers does not increase meaningfully. 
This suggests that customer loyalty is not strongly influencing subscription adoption.

## 3. Implications & Next Steps
This is concerning because loyal customers are the most valuable group to convert into subscribers. 
The lack of conversion highlights an opportunity to introduce new incentives and targeted marketing strategies 
aimed at repeat buyers to increase subscription rates.
